By Ismaila Chafe Abuja – President Muhammadu Buhari has extended heartfelt condolences to the Elebute family on the passing of their father and grandfather, Prof. Emmanuel Elebute, the founder of Lagoon Hospitals and Clinics. The
President, in a statement by his spokesman, Mr Femi Adesina, in Abuja
on Friday, also commiserated with the Nigerian Medical Association (NMA)
and West African College of Surgeons on the death of their
distinguished and highly revered member. President
Buhari paid tribute to Elebute’s championing roles in health education,
medical research and development in the country, through his many
leadership positions in the health sector. He
affirmed that Elebute, onetime had left an impressive legacy in the
field of sciences, healthcare development and delivery in Nigeria, for
others to emulate and build upon. The President prayed that almighty God would receive the late surgeon’s soul and grant him peaceful repose. He
also prayed God to grant the wife of the deceased, Prof. Oyinade
Elebute, children and grandchildren the fortitude to bear the loss.(NAN) By Ismaila Chafe Abuja - President Muhammadu Buhari has congratulated President Macky Sall of Senegal…  By Zubairu Idris Katsina - The All Progressives Congress (APC) presidential candidate, Muhammadu Buhari has…